<item>
            <title>[LU-18939] readahead parameters should allow percentage with sysfs_memparse_total() </title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18939</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;llite.&amp;#42;.max_read_ahead_mb&lt;/tt&gt;,  &lt;tt&gt;llite.&amp;#42;.max_read_ahead_per_file_mb&lt;/tt&gt;, and &lt;tt&gt;llite.&amp;#42;.max_read_ahead_whole_mb&lt;/tt&gt; parameters should be updated to allow being set as a percentage of the total RAM size, so that it is possible to set permanent parameters like &quot;&lt;tt&gt;llite.&amp;#42;.max_read_ahead_mb=25%&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; and &quot;&lt;tt&gt;llite.&amp;#42;.max_read_ahead_per_file_mb=5%&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; that are useful for a variety of different clients.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This can be achieved by using &lt;tt&gt;sysfs_memparse_total()&lt;/tt&gt; to parse the input with a trailing &apos;&lt;tt&gt;%&lt;/tt&gt;&apos; unit, as in &lt;tt&gt;ll_max_cached_mb_seq_write()&lt;/tt&gt;.  It probably does not make sense to allow setting the readahead larger than &lt;tt&gt;cfs_totalram_pages()/2&lt;/tt&gt;, as done today, but it should be possible to set it at &lt;tt&gt;50%&lt;/tt&gt;.  &lt;/p&gt;</description>
